CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1945, pg. 2, reads: "Transferred - Pfc. Roland M. Sawyer of Pittsburgh, a recent graduate of the Adjutant General's School of Separation Classification, has been assigned to Fort George Meade, Ga. Prominent in civic and social circles, Pfc. Sawyer is on military leave from the United States Employment Service. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Roland Sawyer slightly angled to right, wearing jacket with two breast pockets and shoulder flaps, possibly military uniform, in Harris Studio
